Description: 
  HealthMarkers is a unified R toolkit for computing a broad suite 
  of clinical biomarkers from routine data. Out of the box it can calculate:
  - Metabolic markers: insulin‐sensitivity (fasting, OGTT, adipose, tracer/DXA), 
    insulin‐resistance, lipid panels, liver steatosis & fibrosis, anthropometric z‐scores
  - Cardiovascular risk scores and blood pressure indices
  - Pulmonary function indices (spirometry‐based “lung age”, %predicted FEV1, etc.)
  - Biomarker panels from alternate biofluids (urine, saliva, sweat)
  All of these are accessible via a single `health_markers()` dispatcher.
